== 歷史 ==

Canva由[[澳洲|澳洲]]創業家{{tsl|en|Melanie Perkins|梅蘭妮・帕金斯}}、克里夫・歐布雷特（Clifford Obrecht）和技術專家卡梅隆・亞當斯（Cameron Adams）於2012年1月1日在[[雪梨_(城市)|雪梨]]創立，其用戶數於營運首年達75萬。<ref name="rebekah">{{Cite news |url=http://boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/09/15/the-problem-with-going-into-business-with-a-friend/?_r=0 |title=The Problem With Going Into Business With a Friend |last=Campbell |first=Rebekah |date=2014-09-15 |work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]] |language=en-US |dead-url=no |access-date=2014-12-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141221133546/http://boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/09/15/the-problem-with-going-into-business-with-a-friend/?_r=0 |archive-date=2014-12-21 }}</ref>2014年4月，市場行銷、風險投資家[[蓋伊·川崎|蓋伊·川崎]]加入該公司擔任「首席傳教士」{{NoteTag|職務上為品牌推廣人。}}（chief evangelist）。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Guy Kawasaki Joins Australian Design Startup Canva As Chief Evangelist|url=https://social.techcrunch.com/2014/04/16/guy-kawasaki-joins-australian-design-startup-canva-as-chief-evangelist/|date=2014-04-16|accessdate=2021-04-04|author=Pankaj Mishra|work=TechCrunch|language=en|archive-date=2021-04-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210423093026/https://techcrunch.com/2014/04/16/guy-kawasaki-joins-australian-design-startup-canva-as-chief-evangelist/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="陳育晟"/>2015年推出Canva for Work，其著重於市場營銷的素材。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.fastcompany.com/40514362/graphic-design-startup-canva-just-turned-into-a-unicorn|title=Graphic design startup Canva just turned into a unicorn|date=2018-01-08|work=Fast Company|access-date=2018-06-27|language=en-US|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180627230754/https://www.fastcompany.com/40514362/graphic-design-startup-canva-just-turned-into-a-unicorn|archive-date=2018-06-27|dead-url=no}}</ref>2017年，Canva實現營利，付費用戶達29.4萬。<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://techcrunch.com/2018/01/08/new-sequoia-china-investment-values-australian-design-company-canva-at-1-billion/|title=New Sequoia China investment values Australian design company Canva at $1 billion|website=TechCrunch|language=en|author=Jonathan Shieber|date=2018-01-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180627230946/https://techcrunch.com/2018/01/08/new-sequoia-china-investment-values-australian-design-company-canva-at-1-billion/|archive-date=2018-06-27|dead-url=no|accessdate=2021-04-05}}</ref> 

2018年1月，帕金斯宣布獲得美國風險投資公司[[紅杉資本|紅杉資本]]、黑鳥風險投資（Blackbird Ventures）和法利思創投（Felicis Ventures）增資4,000萬[[澳大利亚元|澳大利亚元]]，公司估值達10億澳洲元。<ref name="bbc20180109">{{Cite web |title=The 30-year-old woman who designed a $1bn business |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/business-42552367 |date=2018-01-09 |work=[[BBC_News|BBC News]] |language=en |dead-url=no |first1=Kate |last1=Stanton |first2=Hywel |last2=Griffith |access-date=2018-01-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180728132608/https://www.bbc.com/news/business-42552367 |archive-date=2018-07-28 }}</ref><ref name="abc20180109">{{Cite web |title=Canva: Online design startup joins generally overvalued 'unicorn' club |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2018-01-09/canva-australian-unicorn-1-billion-valuation/9312458 |accessdate=2021-04-06 |date=2018-01-09 |work={{tsl|en|ABC News (Australia)|ABC News (澳洲)|ABC News}} |language=en |dead-url=no |first1=David |last1=Chau |location=Australia |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180112003453/http://www.abc.net.au/news/2018-01-09/canva-australian-unicorn-1-billion-valuation/9312458 |archive-date=2018-01-12 }}</ref>

2019年5月，Canva因[[安全漏洞|安全漏洞]]而遭受[[駭客|駭客]]攻擊，共計有1.39億的用戶資料外洩<ref>{{Cite web |title=Australian tech unicorn Canva suffers security breach |url=https://www.zdnet.com/article/australian-tech-unicorn-canva-suffers-security-breach/ |accessdate=2021-04-06 |author=Catalin Cimpanu |date=2019-05-24 |language=en |website=ZDNet |archive-date=2021-04-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210401003314/https://www.zdnet.com/article/australian-tech-unicorn-canva-suffers-security-breach/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Anny"/>，被公開的資料包括用戶真實姓名、用戶名、[[電子郵件地址|電子郵件地址]]和地理訊息，以及部分用戶[[密碼|密碼]]的[[密碼雜湊函式|雜湊]]。<ref>{{Cite web |title=139 Million Users Hit in Canva Data Breach |url=https://www.tomsguide.com/us/canva-data-breach,news-30165.html |accessdate=2021-04-06 |author=Paul Wagenseil |date=2019-05-24 |language=en |website=Tom's Guide |archive-date=2021-01-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210121052101/https://www.tomsguide.com/us/canva-data-breach,news-30165.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>Canva隨後從技術角度處理漏洞的做法受到讚揚，但其因事發後寄給用戶的電子郵件而被批評，該郵件淡化詳細訊息（該公司所犯錯誤），試圖用自我吹捧的宣傳手法掩蓋。<ref>{{cite news|last1=Smith|first1=Paul|title=Canva criticised after data breach exposed 139m user details|url=https://www.afr.com/technology/canva-criticised-after-data-breach-exposed-139m-user-details-20190526-p51r8i#:~:text=High%20profile%20Australian%20technology%20company,its%20valuation%20soar%20to%20%24US2./|publisher=The Australian Financial Review|access-date=2020-09-05|date=2019-05-26|language=en|subscription=yes|archive-date=2020-09-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200926052513/https://www.afr.com/technology/canva-criticised-after-data-breach-exposed-139m-user-details-20190526-p51r8i#:~:text=High%20profile%20Australian%20technology%20company,its%20valuation%20soar%20to%20%24US2./|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.smartcompany.com.au/startupsmart/analysis/canva-data-breach-response/ |title="Marketing fluff": What startups can learn from Canva's data-breach response |first=Stephanie |date=2019-05-27 |publisher=SmartCompany |language=en |last1=Palmer-Derrin |access-date=2020-09-05 |archive-date=2021-04-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210423093044/https://www.smartcompany.com.au/startupsmart/analysis/canva-data-breach-response/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

